    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to people who create humorous, satiric, obscene, or gang-related writings or drawings that are executed anonymously in public places, usually on walls and typically illegally.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050638/Ganz, Graffiti World: Street Art (2004)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>指在公共區域創作文字或圖案的不具名人氏，作品帶有詼諧、諷刺、枉顧道德或幫派特色，通常為牆上的非法創作。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Verwijst naar mensen die anoniem humoristische, satirische, obscene of bende-gerelateerde teksten of tekeningen maken op openbare plaatsen, meestal op muren en veelal illegaal.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
